Manchester United midfielder, Bruno Fernandes, has said his Portugal team-mate, Cristiano Ronaldo remains interested in the club. Ronaldo spent six seasons at Old Trafford, before departing for Real Madrid in 2009. During his time in Manchester, he won three Premier League titles and the Champions League. Fernandes, who also revealed that Ronaldo influenced his decision to join United in January told the club’s official website: “Every time I speak with him, he asks me how Manchester is and if everything is okay. Everyone knows he spent a lot of time in Manchester, and he has consideration for the club. “He likes the club. I think he won his first Ballon d’Or here, so it’s a club who’ve marked him, for sure.” Fernandes scored 12 goals in all competitions, helping the Red Devils to return to the Champions League.